      <p>Founders who "drown" aren't just losing time; they are losing the mental clarity required to lead. They are operating with 30% of their "RAM" dedicated to their company, while the other 70% is consumed by the friction of unmanaged communication. To survive, you must move from a "Polling" architecture (checking for mail) to an "Interrupt-Driven" architecture (only seeing what matters).</p>

