      <p>The biggest cause of email bloat is "re-reading." You read an email, decide it’s important, but "too complex" to answer now, so you leave it in the inbox. Three hours later, you read it again. By the time you actually reply, you may have read that same email five times. You have effectively quintupled your workload.</p>
      
